description: Congress faces the challenge of selecting a new team in Haryana after its surprise loss. The party aims to expand its social base, moving beyond its traditional Jat-Jatav support. It will choose a combination of state president and legislature party leader to attract other communities, while maintaining existing support.
title: Post-defeat, Congress searches for a new Haryana team

description: For six consecutive days, Indian airlines have faced numerous bomb hoax threats, affecting nearly 90 flights. Major hubs like Mumbai and New Delhi were significantly disrupted. The Bureau of Civil Aviation Security is urging strict adherence to protocols. Initial probes suggest the threats were sent via virtual networks or dark web browsers. The authorities are taking each threat seriously.
title: 20+ flights hit on 6th straight day of bomb hoax threats

description: Even as RJD and Left parties continued to demand "respectable" share despite winning only one seat out of the seven it fought in 2019, both JMM and Congress downplayed the development and said they plan to go ahead with their decision to share 70 among themselves and leave 10 seats for RJD and Left.
title: Cracks in INDIA bloc over Jharkhand seats as RJD, Left demand 'respectable' share

description: Congress is focusing on controlling rebels in the upcoming Maharashtra polls by appointing senior leaders as observers in each region. These observers aim to persuade disappointed ticket aspirants to stay loyal. The strategy follows the Haryana debacle where rebel candidates harmed official prospects. Experienced leaders with strong profiles are given this critical task.
title: Scarred by Haryana loss, Congress focusing on 'rebel factor' in Maharashtra

description: Mumbai crime branch arrested a key accused, Bhagwant Omsingh, in the murder case of NCP leader Baba Siddique, raising total arrests to 10, including the two shooters. Omsingh, who assisted and sheltered shooters, was remanded to police custody. Authorities seek to uncover financial transactions and the source of weapons used in the crime.
title: Scrap dealer 10th accused held in Baba Siddique murder case

description: Uttarakhand HC has directed police to protect a 19-year-old Muslim woman from threats by her family due to her live-in relationship with a Hindu man. The court ordered security after the woman identified nine family members as threats, with next hearing scheduled for October 24.
title: Give protection to interfaith couple, Uttarakhand HC tells police

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma shared a mixed reaction over the Supreme Court's ruling on Section 6A of the Citizenship Act. The judgment, which confirms 1971 as the cut-off date for granting citizenship under the Assam Accord, has elicited both elation and melancholy. Sarma stated that the Assamese people will have to endure ongoing challenges.
title: A blend of joy & sorrow: Himanta on Section 6A verdict

description: A 16-year-old girl in Andhra Pradesh's Kadapa district died after being raped and set on fire by Jakkala Vignesh. The accused, who had a past relationship with the victim and is now married to another woman, was arrested and has confessed. CM Chandrababu Naidu has directed police to expedite the trial and seek capital punishment.
title: Raped & set ablaze, minor dies in Andhra Pradesh hospital

description: The scheduled meetings of AICC's central election and screening committees were cancelled due to disagreements on MVA's seat-sharing formula. Although discussions resumed, no resolution was reached. Congress is prepared for any outcome. Sharad Pawar's involvement is expected to help resolve the dispute soon.
title: Maharashtra muddle? Congress cancels 2 meets as Aaditya talks to Pawar

description: Andhra Pradesh MLC Zakia Khanam, her PRO, and another individual were booked by police for allegedly black-marketing VIP break darshan tickets at Tirumala temple. They reportedly sold tickets for Rs 65,000 each, whereas the original price was Rs 10,500, including a waived donation fee.
title: Andhra MLC booked for selling Rs 10k Tirumala VIP tickets for Rs 65,000

description: Ahead of the elections, the Mahayuti government expands CM Tirth Darshan Yojana, adding dargahs and other minority pilgrimage sites. The scheme provides Rs 30,000 for pilgrimage to senior citizens. Critics view this as an election strategy to gain minority support.
title: Maharashtra adds minority pilgrimage sites to CM scheme ahead of polls

description: Violence in Jiribam, Manipur escalated with suspected militants setting fire to two farmhouses and previous incidents of arson and gunfire, suggesting ethnic tensions. Security forces intervened quickly, rescuing a local leader, while the attackers escaped. The unrest follows recent ethnic discussions in New Delhi.
title: Militants set on fire 2 farmhouses in Manipur

description: UP Police faces criticism over alleged trigger-happy actions and staged encounters, defended by DGP Prashant Kumar who insists due process and court guidelines are followed. Recent convictions and asset seizures under strict laws highlight a zero-tolerance policy against crime.
title: ‘Contrary to perception, UP police not trigger-happy force’

description: Residents of riot-hit Maharajganj, Bahraich, rushed to dismantle parts of their properties following a PWD demolition notice due to alleged encroachment. Traders quickly emptied shops, while some questioned why only specific locations were targeted. Notices were served on 23 homes and shops, including properties owned by Abdul Hameed, a suspect in recent communal violence.
title: Bahraich villagers fear bulldozer action, pull down own properties

description: Israeli brigade commander Colonel Ahsan Daksa was killed in a blast in Jabalia, northern Gaza, while fighting Hamas. Daksa, a Druze community member, was appointed four months ago and was leading the offensive. His death marks one of the highest-ranking Israeli officer fatalities in the year-long conflict.
title: Israel confirms death of IDF commander in battle in northern Gaza

description: A mystery illness in Udaipur's Kotra area has led to the deaths of 17 children over 30 days. The affected children showed symptoms of fever, cold, and cough. The Rajasthan health department is investigating the cause, suspecting seasonal diseases and improper treatment as potential factors.
title: Mystery illness claims lives of 17 kids in 30 days in Rajasthan

description: LTIMindtree, India's sixth-largest tech services firm, focuses on larger clients and AI integration, securing its largest-ever deal with a U.S. manufacturer. Despite revenue growth, concerns about seasonal factors and macroeconomic challenges remain. The company aims for a robust $5 billion deal pipeline.
title: LTIMindtree win its largest deal in history: We are now ..., says COO

description: BJP retains 71 sitting MLAs on its first candidate list for the Maharashtra assembly polls, favoring old guard over new faces. Key nominees include Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis and Chandrashekhar Bawankule. Despite some LS poll losses, many candidates got the nod, showing RSS's influence in decisions. Notable replacements include jailed MLA Ganpat Gaikwad’s wife, Sulabha.
title: BJP retains 71 MLAs in first Maharashtra list of 99

description: Donald Trump, in a campaign move, visited a McDonald's in Pennsylvania, where he donned an apron to make and distribute french fries to his supporters. This stunt targeted Kamala Harris’s claim of working at a McDonald's, which Trump disputes, calling her 'Lyin' Kamala.' Critics mocked Trump for the act on social media.
title: Old Donald McMocks Kamala making french fries

description: Outgoing Indian high commissioner to Canada, Sanjay Verma, accused Canadian PM Justin Trudeau of damaging India-Canada relations based on intel rather than evidence, and encouraging Khalistan extremists. Verma, who was recalled amid criminal allegations, denies any wrongdoing and criticizes Canada for not sharing evidence and following proper procedures.
title: Trudeau destroyed ties on basis of mere intel: Ex-envoy

description: In a grave attack in Ganderbal, Kashmir, Pakistani terrorists killed six construction workers and a doctor, the deadliest assault on civilians in decades. This incident occurred near Apco Infratech's tunnel project and highlighted renewed terrorist targeting of non-locals. Union Home Minister Amit Shah condemned the attack, promising stern action against those responsible.
title: Doctors among 7 workers killed in Kashmir tunnel site terrorist attack

description: New Zealand won their first Women's T20 World Cup by defeating South Africa by 32 runs in Dubai. Led by Sophie Devine, they posted 158/5, with Amelia Kerr (43) and Brooke Halliday (38) making key contributions. Kerr also excelled with the ball, taking 3/24. The victory capped off a momentous day for New Zealand cricket, as the men's team also achieved their first Test win in India in 36 years earlier in the day.
title: New Zealand clinch maiden Women's T20 World Cup title

description: Two labourers were killed and two injured in Ganderbal district, J&K, after terrorists fired on a construction camp. This marks the fifth targeted attack on non-natives in Kashmir this year. Security forces are actively searching for the attackers. Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha and other leaders have strongly condemned the attack, while expressing solidarity with the victims' families.
title: 2 labourers killed, 2 injured in terrorist attack in J&K's Ganderbal

description: India's High Commissioner to Canada, Sanjay Kumar Verma, denies involvement in the murder of Hardeep Singh Nijjar, asserting that accusations from Prime Minister Justin Trudeau are politically motivated. Verma criticizes Trudeau for damaging bilateral relations based on unsubstantiated intelligence rather than concrete evidence.
title: Trudeau has destroyed Canada-India political ties: Outgoing envoy Sanjay Verma

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi launched 23 development projects worth Rs 6,700 crore in Varanasi, focusing on infrastructure and regional connectivity. Key projects include RJ Sankara Eye Hospital and expansion of Bagdogra Airport, which aims to enhance sustainable aviation capacity and cater to increasing passenger demands.
title: PM Modi launches several projects worth Rs 6,700cr in Varanasi

description: Anu Sharma, a Google software engineer, revealed on X (Twitter) that she was rejected from a job role for having qualifications that far exceeded the requirements.
title: Google techie, rejected for being 'too good', shares her rejection letter

description: Indian cricketing legend Virender Sehwag received an outpouring of birthday wishes on social media as he turned 46. Icons like Sachin Tendulkar, Yuvraj Singh, and Saurav Ganguly shared heartfelt messages celebrating his contributions to cricket. Renowned for his explosive batting, Sehwag's illustrious career includes holding records in both Test and ODI formats.
title: Sachin teases Sehwag with a witty birthday post

description: Donald Trump's recent public speeches have included bizarre digressions, such as commenting on deceased golfer Arnold Palmer's anatomy and using vulgar language. These behaviors are raising concerns about his mental state among both critics and supporters as the presidential race remains competitive.
title: Trump incoherence to incontinence: The schlong and short of it

description: Kamala Harris faces criticism over a new campaign ad targeting black men's voting behavior via Instagram and Snapchat. The ad, aimed largely at women, has sparked backlash for being seen as patronizing. As the election nears, both Harris and Trump intensify their campaigns, urging early voting with celebrity endorsements.
title: 'Don't get popped': Kamala under fire over campaign ad targeting black men's love life

description: Somy Ali seeks peace following Lawrence Bishnoi’s allegations against Salman Khan. Neetu Kapoor finds solace in work after Rishi Kapoor's death. Rumors lead Twinkle Khanna to temporarily leave Akshay Kumar. Ekta and Shobha Kapoor face legal issues over 'Gandi Baat' content. Diljit Dosanjh makes history on Billboard Canada charts.
title: Somy Ali on why she wanted to call Lawrence Bishnoi & more: Top 5 news

description: The Uniform Civil Code (UCC), set to be implemented in Uttarakhand on November 9, mandates marriage registration within six months and live-in relationship registration within one month. It also entails property rights for parents upon an earning child's death and proposes strict penalties for non-compliance and false information.
title: Uttarakhand UCC: Registering live-in relations must within month of rollout

description: The Sheopur Kuno National Park in Madhya Pradesh announces that a female cheetah named Veera is pregnant, marking a significant milestone for the cheetah project. Veera, who has previously wandered outside the park, is expected to deliver soon, bringing renewed optimism for wildlife conservation. Kuno currently houses 24 cheetahs, including 12 cubs. Shifted from South Africa, Veera, who is nearly 5 years old.
title: Female Cheetah pregnant: CM Mohan Yadav shares good news from Kuno

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi launched 23 development projects worth Rs 6,700 crore in Varanasi, focusing on infrastructure and regional connectivity. Key projects include RJ Sankara Eye Hospital and expansion of Bagdogra Airport, which aims to enhance sustainable aviation capacity and cater to increasing passenger demands.
title: PM Modi launches several projects worth Rs 6,700cr in Varanasi

description: Mumbai Police arrested Bhagwant Singh, the tenth accused in the assassination of ex-minister Baba Siddique. Singh allegedly helped the shooters obtain accommodation and weapons. Suspects revealed they had multiple failed attempts to kill both Baba and Zeeshan Siddique, using YouTube videos for firearm training. ​​During interrogation, the suspects revealed they had orders to kill both Baba and Zeeshan Siddique.
title: Baba Siddique murder: Accused who gave shelter, weapons to shooters arrested

description: A 30-year-old man died after fainting while helping his girlfriend who had slit her wrist. He was pronounced dead at Kailash Deepak Hospital, and the police suspect a possible cardiac arrest. The girlfriend was admitted for her injuries in Anand Vihar, Delhi. The man's autopsy is being conducted for further investigation.
title: Delhi man dies after girlfriend sends self-harm video

description: The Bombay Stock Exchange and National Stock Exchange in India will host a special 'Muhurat Trading' session on November 1, from 6 pm to 7 pm, marking Diwali and the new Samvat 2081. This one-hour trading window is seen as auspicious for financial prosperity. Market analysts predict volatility due to the brief session, emphasizing symbolic participation over profits.
title: BSE, NSE announce Diwali Muhurat Trading: Check date and time

description: Allrounder Washington Sundar on Sunday was added to Team India’s squad for the second and third Test match against New Zealand.
title: Washington Sundar added to India squad vs New Zealand

description: Thomas 'TJ' Hoover II, 36, after a drug overdose in October 2021, was declared brain dead but then miraculously regained consciousness at the moment when doctors were about to remove his heart for organ donation. This incident has prompted investigations and raised serious ethical concerns.
title: Brain dead man comes back to life as doctors prepared to remove his heart

description: RJD leader Manoj Kumar Jha hinted at solo contest in Jharkhand assembly polls due to dissatisfaction with seat allocation in the INDIA bloc. Despite a possible solo run, RJD plans to support bloc candidates in 60-62 seats and prioritize areas where it was strong in previous elections.  "Less than 12-13 seats are not acceptable, the RJD has a strong hold on 18-20 seats," Jha said.
title: 'Will not let boat sink, but ... ': RJD hints at going solo in Jharkhand polls

description: New Zealand achieved a momentous victory over India in the first Test of a three-match series, marking their first win on Indian soil since 1988. Despite India's strong second innings, New Zealand's disciplined performance secured a win by eight wickets. The second Test commences in Pune on October 24, followed by the final match in Mumbai.
title: 'Dil dukha hai par ...': Viral memes after New Zealand wins 1st Test

description: India captain Rohit Sharma dismisses the notion that the team's performance in the first Test against New Zealand, where they collapsed for 46 runs, defines their abilities. He highlights the team’s strong second-innings effort and emphasizes staying composed and united. Rohit also praises Sarfaraz Khan's performance and stresses careful management of Rishabh Pant's recovery process.
title: 'Those three hours...': Rohit defends team after collapse

description: Zeeshan Siddique, son of the late NCP leader Baba Siddique, addressed his father's killers on social media, stating the fight for justice remains ongoing. Asserting his courage and commitment, Zeeshan reaffirmed his dedication to the people of Vandre East, indicating he remains unafraid and ready to continue his father's legacy.
title: 'Fight is far from over': Baba Siddique's son dares killers

description: Karwa Chauth Moonrise Timing 2024 Karwa Chauth, a festival for married Hindu women, will be observed on October 20, 2024. The day includes fasting from sunrise until moonrise, with specific rituals and prayers for the husbands' longevity. Moonrise times differ by city, and the fast is concluded through traditional ceremonies and family celebrations.
title: Karwa Chauth: Know moonrise timing in your city & process to break fast

description: KL Rahul's pitch-touching gesture after India's Test defeat to New Zealand has sparked speculation about his future in the format. His poor recent form, combined with the likely return of Shubman Gill and Sarfaraz Khan's strong performance, could see him dropped for the next match. The viral clip of Rahul touching the pitch has further fueled these rumors, with some fans even suggesting the right-hander could be considering retirement from Test cricket.
title: KL Rahul sparks retirement rumours

description: A loud explosion startled Rohini residents Sunday morning near a CRPF school in Paschim Vihar. Houses shook, white smoke filled the air, and nearby structures suffered damage. Authorities suspect a crude bomb; investigations are ongoing. No casualties reported, but residents remain anxious.
title: 'Chemical-like smell, smoke everywhere': Delhi locals recount panic after blast

description: WWE Hall of Famer Hulk Hogan has again endorsed Donald Trump for the 2024 US Presidential Elections, despite polls favoring Kamala Harris. Hogan expressed his confidence in Trump’s business acumen and predicted a landslide victory while appearing on Fox News this Saturday night. His support for Trump is long and well known.
title: Hogan backs Trump for presidential election while polls favour Harris

description: New Zealand achieves a historic Test win in India, their first since 1988, after successfully chasing a tough target on the final day in Bengaluru. India's lowest home total of 46 in the first innings set the tone, despite their second innings recovery. New Zealand joined England and Australia as the only teams to defeat India at home since 2013.
title: 'This game will knock you down, but...': Rishabh Pant

description: IDF claims that former Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar's wife, Samar Muhammad Abu Zamar, was seen with a $32,000 Hermès Birkin handbag as they fled into a tunnel before the October 7 attack on Israel. Lieutenant Colonel Avichay Adraee highlighted the wealth disparity between Sinwar's family and ordinary Gazan citizens. Sinwar was killed by Israeli forces in Gaza on Wednesday.
title: Yahya Sinwar's wife carried $32,000 handbag in tunnel escape footage: IDF

description: India's pacer Mohammed Shami undertakes an intensive bowling session under coach Abhishek Nayar’s supervision following the first Test defeat to New Zealand. His participation in the Australia's Test series remains uncertain due to ongoing recovery from knee swelling post-ankle surgery.
title: Shami bowls in nets after India's defeat in Bengaluru
Threats to flights keep pouring in; no improvement in over week-old crisis

description: Yuvika Chaudhary and Prince Narula have welcomed a baby girl. Prince's father confirmed the news expressing his happiness. The couple's love story began on Bigg Boss 9, leading to their marriage in 2018. Yuvika chose IVF to ensure their family planning didn't affect Prince's career. Both are excited about this new phase.
title: Prince Narula and Yuvika Chaudhary welcome a baby girl

description: A woman was allegedly gangraped by four men after they offered her a lift in an autorickshaw in Nizamabad. They took her to Dichpally where the assault occurred. She reported the incident to the police the next morning, and an investigation is underway to trace the perpetrators through the vehicle's registration number.
title: 'Alone at bus stand, offered lift': Woman gangraped by four in auto

description: India's billionaire count has risen significantly, with Bengaluru housing some of the wealthiest individuals. Azim Premji tops the city's rich list with Rs 1,90,700 crore. Other notable billionaires include Irfan Razack, Nithin Kamath, S Gopalakrishnan, and Infosys' NR Narayana Murthy, highlighting Bengaluru's prominence in software, real estate, and financial sectors.
title: Wipro’s Azim Premji to Infosys’ Narayana Murthy: 5 richest people in B'luru

description: A viral video from Odisha captures a tense moment where a girl, under her family's pressure, reluctantly unveils her hidden boyfriend within an iron suitcase. Amidst the family's disapproval, the girl asserts that they are married, pleading for the boy's safety, sparking varied reactions online.
title: Odisha girl locks boyfriend in iron suitcase, video goes viral

description: India's loss to New Zealand in the first Test in Bengaluru impacted their ICC World Test Championship points percentage, dropping it from 74.24 to 68.06. India remain on top but now faces closer competition from Australia and Sri Lanka for the WTC Final spot.
title: India loosen grip on WTC Final spot after defeat vs NZ

description: The US government is investigating the leak of classified documents detailing Israel’s military actions against Iran. Originating from GEOINT and NSA, these Top Secret documents were shared online, prompting a probe into the breach and concerns over further sensitive information exposure.
title: Leaked US documents reveal Israel’s plans for strike on Iran

description: Vikash Yadav's family expressed shock over allegations of his involvement in a plot to kill Khalistani terrorist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun. They claim the charges are baseless and fabricated. Despite the US Department of Justice’s indictment alleging Yadav’s role in the failed assassination, his relatives maintain his innocence and question the validity of the accusations.
title: 'Working for country': Vikash Yadav's family rejects Pannun murder plot allegations

description: Gopal Joshi, brother of Union minister Pralhad Joshi, and his nephew Ajay were arrested by Bengaluru police following a cheating complaint. Tracked to Kolhapur and Pune respectively, they were questioned in Hubballi post-raid. Pralhad Joshi claimed he had disowned Gopal 30 years ago.
title: Union min Pralhad Joshi’s brother and nephew arrested in Rs 2 crore scam

description: Fawzia Sido, a Yazidi woman abducted by ISIS at 11, recounted the horror of being forced to eat baby flesh during her captivity. After days of starvation, she and others unknowingly consumed the gruesome meal. A covert mission by Israel, the U.S., and Iraq finally rescued her, though many Yazidis remain missing.
title: 'Had a weird taste': Freed ISIS hostage, says they were made to eat babies

description: Rohit Sharma became the first Indian captain in 36 years to lose a Test match to New Zealand at home, as the Kiwis secured victory by 8 wickets in Bengaluru.  New Zealand's last Test victory came at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai way back in 1988. Reflecting on the defeat after the match, Rohit said they knew what was ahead after India were bowled out for 46 runs in their first innings.
title: 'When you are 350 behind ... ': Rohit Sharma reflects on defeat to NZ

description: Rachin Ravindra's century and Bangalore's inclement weather played key roles in New Zealand's historic Test win over India. After India was dismissed for 46 in challenging conditions, Ravindra's 134 helped the Kiwis gain a massive lead. Despite India’s efforts, New Zealand chased the 107-run target, marking a rare home defeat for India.
title: 1st Test: How Bengaluru weather 'helped' New Zealand defeat India

description: New Zealand achieved a historic eight-wicket win in Bengaluru, their first victory on Indian soil in 36 years. Despite India's strong bowling efforts in the morning session on the final day, led by Jasprit Bumrah, Rachin Ravindra and Will Young secured the win. New Zealand now lead the three-match series 1-0.
title: Rachin stars in NZ's first Test win in India in 36 years

description: Kiccha Sudeep's mother, Saroja, passed away at 83 after battling age-related ailments. Admitted to a private hospital in Bengaluru due to breathing issues, she breathed her last today. Her final rites are scheduled at Wilson Garden crematorium, with friends and fans offering condolences.
title: Kiccha Sudeep's mother Saroja passes away at 83

description: Neeraj Chopra, visiting Lucknow, shared his memories and future goals, aiming for a 90-metre throw. He highlighted injury concerns affecting his training. Neeraj also spoke on his coach Klaus Bartonietz retiring and emphasized the importance of domestic competition and training abroad. He stressed the significance of sports for health and upcoming athletes for the 2036 Olympics.
title: My target is to throw beyond 90m mark: Neeraj Chopra

description: A 19-year-old BBA student named Shravya from Bengaluru committed suicide on Saturday at her Chamarajpet home after a fight with her elder sister over a bedsheet. Despite not leaving a death note, her gymmates and trainer indicated she was distressed by her parents' frequent arguments.
title: 19-year-old BBA student ends life over bedsheet row in Bengaluru

description: Delhi's government has attributed worsening air quality in Anand Vihar to buses from Uttar Pradesh. Chief minister Atishi and environment minister Gopal Rai conducted inspections and emphasized the need for joint efforts with UP to mitigate pollution, urging measures like water sprinkling and improved emission controls.
title: 'Doubling Delhi's pollution': AAP blames UP buses

description: Former Delhi minister Satyendar Jain claims he was falsely accused of receiving a massage in Tihar Jail; he insists it was physiotherapy for severe leg pain. Jain alleges mistreatment, including solitary confinement and lack of amenities, during his incarceration. BJP dismisses his claims as fabricated stories.
title: ‘My therapy was called massage’: Satyendar Jain
'Congressman by birth': Ex-Haryana min Ajay Yadav makes another U-turn

description: For the first time, a student named Sagar TS has enrolled in a Kannada-medium mechanical engineering programme at Maharaja Institute of Technology, Mysore. The initiative, launched in 2021-22, has struggled to attract students, with around 13,000 CET seats still vacant for English-medium courses. Reservations in state government jobs were suggested to boost interest.
title: At long last, Kannada medium engineering course draws one student

description: A retired scientist and his wife in Delhi fell victim to a daylight robbery by men posing as courier agents. The robbers ransacked their home, stealing about Rs 4 crore in cash and valuables. The incident raises concerns of potential insider involvement and highlights the issue of senior citizen safety in the city.
title: Ex-scientist, wife robbed of Rs 4 crore valuables by ‘courier agents’

description: Microsoft's Integrated Visual Augmentation System (IVAS) goggles, intended for the US Army, face price challenges with a current projection of $80,000 per set. The Army has called for substantial cost reductions. Successful cost management could lead to a $21.9 billion contract over a decade if production moves forward.
title: US Army makes a 'price request' to Microsoft for these Goggles

description: Enforcement Directorate officials find that the disputed Kesare land still belongs to Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah's wife, BM Parvathi. Despite the land's acquisition by the Mysore Urban Development Authority, Parvathi's name remains on records, complicating the investigation into potential negligence and mismanagement.
title: Karnataka CM’s wife still shown as owner of disputed land on revenue records

description: An elderly couple, Linga Reddy, 80, and his wife Urmila, 75, were found murdered in their Hyderabad home. Police suspect a robbery motive as thousands of dollars and gold ornaments are missing. The couple had last been seen on Thursday, and their bodies were discovered on Saturday by a family friend. CCTV footage is being reviewed.
title: Elderly couple found murdered in Hyderabad, US $2,000, jewels missing

description: SpaceX opposes interference claims by Omnispace in an FCC filing, deeming their technical analyses flawed and defending its direct-to-cellular service. Arguing for the public benefits, SpaceX seeks to emphasize that Omnispace's assertions lack support and aim to undermine competition.
title: SpaceX complains against military supplier for what Musk calls ‘dirty trick’

description: The Indian Army and J&K Police conducted an anti-infiltration operation in the Uri sector following intelligence inputs. Suspicious activity was met with gunfire. Two terrorists responsible for grenade attacks and anti-national activities were arrested in Poonch, and a laborer was found dead in Shopian.
title: Army, J&K police exchange fire with terrorists in a joint operation along LOC

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali criticized Pakistan A’s Sufiyan Muqeem for his unsportsmanlike behavior during a match against India A, emphasizing the need for young players to respect opponents. The incident involved Muqeem making a 'silence gesture' after dismissing India's Abhishek Sharma, leading to a heated exchange. Despite the tension, India A won by 7 runs.
title: 'Aap gaaliyan de rahe hain...': Basit blasts Pak pacer for send-off

description: Virat Kohli, revered for his devotion to Test cricket, often engages with the crowd to boost team morale, especially during critical moments. His enthusiastic gestures and crowd interaction, displayed in a recent match against New Zealand, highlight his passionate connection with fans and leadership on the field.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli asks crowd to cheer for Team India

description: IIT Roorkee faced backlash after students from Radha Krishna Bhawan hostel claimed unhygienic conditions with rats in the mess kitchen. A video showing rodents in utensils went viral, prompting an official investigation. The institute refuted claims of contaminated food, calling it a deliberate misrepresentation, yet students remained skeptical about the hygiene standards.
title: Watch: Rats found swimming in IIT-Roorkee mess food, students protest

description: Sarfaraz Khan, after hitting his maiden Test century against New Zealand, expressed his joy of playing alongside Virat Kohli, who motivated him to stay confident. Sarfaraz's 150, paired with Rishabh Pant's 99, helped India post a strong 462 in the second innings, setting up a thrilling final day as New Zealand chase 107 runs.
title: 'Virat Kohli was telling me to...': Sarfaraz shares surreal experience

description: YouTuber Gaurav Taneja, known as Flying Beast, addresses rumors of marital issues with wife Ritu Rathee. Amid divorce speculations, Taneja shares an Instagram post emphasizing privacy. The rumors began after a viral video showing Rathee seeking relationship advice. Taneja also posted family pictures from Durga Puja celebrations.
title: Gaurav Taneja shares post with Ritu Rathee: Message is clear, jab tumhare ...

description: Four firefighters sustained minor shrapnel injuries after a Ukrainian drone attacked an industrial area in Dzerzhinsk, Russia. The incident was part of a broader assault where Russian air defense intercepted 110 drones, including in Moscow and other western regions, causing temporary fires and disruptions. Kyiv has previously said that its air attacks focus on infrastructure vital to Russia's war efforts in response to ongoing airstrikes on Ukraine.
title: Russia destroys 110 Ukraine drones, four fighters injured in Dzerzhinsk
'Nari Shakti blessings': PM Modi after Odisha tribal woman sends Rs 100

description: A powerful blast near CRPF School in Rohini's Sector 14 on Sunday morning caused extensive damage to the school wall, nearby shop windows, and a parked car, without any injuries. Police and experts, including the Crime Team, Forensic Science Laboratory, and Bomb Disposal Squad, are investigating the cause of the explosion while the area remains cordoned off.
title: Blast in Delhi: Explosion reported outside CRPF school in Rohini

description: A BJP leader's son married a Pakistani girl via an online 'nikah' due to visa issues caused by political tensions. The groom's father arranged the virtual ceremony, with both families participating from their respective countries. Shia religious leaders conducted the wedding, and the groom hopes his wife can obtain an Indian visa soon.
title: BJP corporator's son marries Pakistani woman in online 'nikah' ceremony

description: Karwa Chauth, a festival celebrated with love, devotion, and the beautiful bond between married couples, is a special occasion for those who observe a day-long fast for their partner's longevity and well-being. This year, Karwa Chauth falls on October 20. On this auspicious day,
title: Happy Karwa Chauth: Wishes, messages, quotes, images & more

description: Prabowo Subianto, sworn in as Indonesia's eighth president on Sunday, took his oath on the Quran in Jakarta. The ceremony saw attendance from global leaders and supporters. Subianto, a former defense minister and rival to ex-President Widodo, promises continuity of existing policies.
title: Prabowo Subianto takes oath as eighth president of Indonesia

description: Former cricketer Mohammad Kaif praised Sarfaraz Khan for his 150-run performance in the second innings of the first Test against New Zealand. Despite fitness concerns, Kaif emphasized Sarfaraz's skills. Sarfaraz's century came in a crucial moment, aiding India in the match. His journey to the Indian Test team is marked by his domestic cricket successes.
title: 'He doesn't have a gym body but...': Kaif after Sarfaraz's knock

description: AWS CEO Matt Garman announced a strict five-day office work policy from January 2025, emphasizing that remote work hinders innovation and collaboration. Garman urges employees who disagree to seek opportunities elsewhere. Despite backlash, he insists that in-person interactions are essential for company culture and driving innovation, distinguishing Amazon from its more flexible tech peers.
title: Amazon cloud boss: The 5-day RTO mandate is important for ...

description: A day after a school was set ablaze, suspected militants carried out a gun and bomb attack near Borobekra Police Station in Jiribam, Manipur. Central security forces responded promptly, and civilians have been relocated. No casualties have been reported in the current unrest.
title: Militants attack Manipur thana day after setting school on fire

description: Pakistan's young fast bowler Ihsanullah believes Naseem Shah is superior to India's Jasprit Bumrah, sparking a debate among cricket enthusiasts. He defended his stance by highlighting Naseem's World Cup performance, despite Bumrah's established track record. Former Pakistan captain Babar Azam also prefers Naseem for high-pressure situations, showing growing support for the young pacer.
title: Watch: 'Pakistan ke pass Bumrah se accha bowler hai'

description: Governor R N Ravi faced backlash for omitting 'Dravida' from Tamil Thaai Vaazhthu during a Hindi event, igniting criticism from various political leaders. Participating in Tamil University’s convocation, Ravi stood up for the original version. Leaders accused him of creating controversies for attention, while discussions on language policies and spirituality in politics ensued.
title: TN governor faces the music after omisson of ‘dravida’ from Tamil anthem

description: In East Delhi's Jagatpuri, a woman attempted suicide after a fight with her boyfriend, Arjun. She filmed the act and sent it to him, prompting Arjun to rush her to the hospital. However, he succumbed to a cardiac arrest upon seeing her bleeding. Doctors saved the woman.
title: Delhi girl survives wrist cut but lover, overcome by sight of blood, dies

description: Individuals are advised to navigate challenges today with patience and introspection. Emotional balance, strategic planning, effective communication, and self-care are emphasized. Watch for emotional intensity and stay true to your values. Seek relaxation and positive interactions as key moments for personal and professional growth.
title: Numerology predictions: Read your personalised forecast for numbers 1 to 9

description: Lionel Messi's second hat-trick of the week and Luis Suarez's double saw Inter Miami thrash New England Revolution 6-2, setting a new Major League Soccer points record. Miami, having already clinched the Supporters' Shield, finished the regular season with 75 points, surpassing New England's 2021 record of 74.
title: Messi hits another hat-trick as Miami break MLS points record

description: Israel releases footage showing Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar in a tunnel under his home, preparing for the October 7 attack. The video shows Sinwar and his family moving supplies into the underground hideout in Khan Younis. Sinwar, later killed by an Israeli tank strike, had played a key role in orchestrating the attack.
title: Watch: Hamas chief Sinwar in tunnel hours before Oct 7 attack on Israel

description: Eight flights to and from Delhi's Indira Gandhi International Airport received bomb threats via social media on Saturday. Authorities conducted thorough security checks and found nothing suspicious. The affected flights included six international and two domestic, causing inconvenience but ensuring the safety of customers and crew as per standard procedures.
title: Eight flights linked to IGI Airport get hoax bomb threats on social media

description: Novak Djokovic expressed deep gratitude to Rafael Nadal during their final match at the Six Kings Slam event in Saudi Arabia. Djokovic honored their intense rivalry and Nadal's contributions to tennis, as the Spaniard prepares to retire after the Davis Cup Finals next month.
title: Watch: Novak Djokovic expresses gratitude to Rafael Nadal

description: CM Mamata Banerjee has reached out to fasting junior doctors in Kolkata, promising to address their demands within three to four months. Despite her plea to end the strike, the doctors plan to continue their protest until they see tangible actions from the government.
title: RG Kar issue: Mamata’s 1-hour call sets up another govt-doctor meet

description: Shrikant Pangarkar, accused in the Gauri Lankesh murder case and currently on bail, is set to lead CM Shinde-led Shiv Sena's poll campaign in Maharashtra's Jalna assembly constituency. Despite facing criminal charges, Pangarkar, a long-time Shiv Sena member, has been assigned fresh responsibilities for the 2024 assembly polls.
title: Gauri Lankesh murder accused to head Shiv Sena poll campaign in Jalna seat

description: A state government employee, P Sakkarai, was convicted of bribery and sentenced to one year in prison, 15 years after being caught accepting a 1,000 bribe from loan applicant E John. Trapped by the DVAC in 2009, Sakkarai was fined 1,000 on top of the jail term.
title: Rs 1,000 bribe lands Tamil Nadu govt servant, 61, in jail for 1 year

description: Madhya Pradesh high court orders the transfer of Bhalumada police station staff to locations at least 900km away to prevent conspiracies. The DGP is directed to ensure all police station rooms have CCTV with audio. The court also mandates Rs 1.2 lakh compensation to the victim.
title: High court orders transfer of cops 900km away
Nawab Malik's candidature unacceptable: BJP

description: Vijaya Kishore Rahatkar is appointed as the new chairperson of the National Commission for Women, succeeding Rekha Sharma. Rahatkar, previously the Maharashtra Women's Commission chief, will commence her tenure immediately. The Ministry of Women and Child Development also confirmed Archana Majumdar's appointment as an NCW member for three years.
title: Vijaya Kishore Rahatkar appointed new NCW chief

description: BJP has released its first list of candidates for 66 of the 68 constituencies they plan to contest in the Jharkhand polls, naming veteran leaders and former MPs. Major candidates include state president Babulal Marandi and former CM Champai Soren, reinforcing local strength and incumbent positions.
title: Champai Soren, Sita Soren, Babulal Marandi in BJP first list of 66 seats out of 68

description: An unprecedented surge of hoax bomb threats targeted 30-40 Indian flights and five Delta Air Lines flights on Saturday, marking the highest in a day. These threats caused significant disruptions and delays due to necessary security checks. Authorities emphasized the robust safety protocols in place and urged passengers to continue flying without fear.
title: Aviation security chief meets airline CEOs over bomb threats

description: Haridwar district administration demolished a 15-20 year-old illegally constructed mazar in Mirpur village after the investigation revealed its illegality. The land, owned by the rehabilitation department, was leased for agriculture but had an expired lease. Despite prior notice, occupants failed to remove the structure, leading to its demolition.
title: 'Illegal' mazar demolished in Haridwar after locals complain

description: The INDIA bloc's campaign in Jharkhand faces turmoil as JMM and Congress announce a seat-sharing deal excluding RJD and Left parties. Tejashwi Yadav's absence highlights RJD's discontent. Criticism emerges over lack of consultation, with RJD and CPI-ML pushing for greater inclusion and clarity.
title: RJD fumes after JMM, Congress declare Jharkhand seat deal

description: In Kota district, a Class 5 student sustained a fractured arm after a teacher allegedly beat her with a stick. The incident was reported to Education Minister Madan Dilawar, who directed police to investigate and ordered a departmental inquiry. The teacher is accused of attacking the student after she failed to follow instructions properly.
title: Govt teacher beats up Class 5 girl in Kota, leaves her with fractured arm

description: The United Forum of Bank Unions in Maharashtra has declared a strike on Nov 16 to protest the unsafe working conditions faced by bank employees during the implementation of the 'Mukhyamantri Mazhi Ladki Bahin Yojana.' The unions cited incidents of harassment and assaults by scheme beneficiaries and local politicians.
title: Bank unions allege ‘unsafe’ work setting over Ladki Bahin

description: Life threats against Salman Khan by gangster Lawrence Bishnoi keep recurring, drawing attention to unresolved 1998 poaching cases involving Khan. The Bishnoi community remains divided, with some demanding an apology from Khan, while others seek prosecution. Law enforcement faces challenges due to these ongoing threats.
title: Gangster Lawrence Bishnoi’s vendetta reignites poaching case debate

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 20, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today: Read your astrological predictions
